# Referral System Audit & Fix Plan

After fully auditing all three referral flows (Products, Services, Courses), here is a complete breakdown of what works, what is broken, and what needs to be fixed.

---

## Summary of Findings

### ✅ What Works

| Area | Status |
|------|--------|
| **Products** — referral code validated at checkout | ✅ Works |
| **Products** — `referralCodeUsed` saved to Order | ✅ Works |
| **Products** — points awarded on Delivered + isPaid (instant path for non-returnable items) | ✅ Works |
| **Products** — both referrer and referee credited | ✅ Works |
| **Courses** — referral code saved to `CourseApplication.referralCode` | ✅ Works |
| **Courses** — points awarded on first fee payment | ✅ Works |
| **Courses** — both referrer and referee get wallet + WalletTransaction | ✅ Works |
| **Services** — referral code validated and saved to `referralCodeUsed` | ✅ Works |

---

### ❌ Bugs Found

#### Bug 1 — Services: Referral NEVER triggered (Critical)
**File:** [services.js](file:///d:/final/CMGROUPS/backend/src/routes/services.js) line 487  
**Problem:** The service referral trigger has this condition:
```js
if (status === 'Completed' && req.body.isPaid === true) {
```
The admin updates service status via `PATCH /api/services/:id/status`. The request body contains `status`, `estimatedPrice`, `finalPrice`, etc. — but `isPaid` is **never sent by the admin panel**. So `req.body.isPaid` is always `undefined`, meaning this block **never runs**. Services referral is completely broken.

**Fix:** Remove `isPaid` check from the condition. Service referral should trigger when status becomes `'Delivered'` (when service is finished and returned to customer), not `'Completed'` (which is internal status). Or use `'Completed'` but drop the `isPaid` guard.

#### Bug 2 — Services: Wrong `source` field on Referral record (Critical)
**File:** [services.js](file:///d:/final/CMGROUPS/backend/src/routes/services.js) line 507  
**Problem:** When checking for an existing referral to prevent duplicates:
```js
where: { refereeId: fullBooking.userId, referrerId, source: 'shopping' }
```
The source check is hardcoded to `'shopping'`, not `'service'`. So:
- It won't find an existing service referral → allows duplicate rewards.
- The [Referral](file:///d:/final/CMGROUPS/frontend/src/lib/api.js#423-424) record created for services also doesn't set `source` (defaults to `'shopping'`), making it invisible in referral stats under the `service` category.

**Fix:** Change the `source` to `'service'` in both the findFirst query and the referral.create call.

#### Bug 3 — Services: Referral record missing `source` and `orderId` context
**File:** [services.js](file:///d:/final/CMGROUPS/backend/src/routes/services.js) ~line 523–531  
**Problem:** The `referral.create` call inside the transaction is missing the `source: 'service'` field, so it defaults to `'shopping'`. The booking ID is also not linked.

**Fix:** Add `source: 'service'` and link `orderId` to the booking ID (or add a `bookingId` field if needed — but the schema doesn't have one, so we can omit orderId).

#### Bug 4 — Products: [calculateOrderReferralPoints](file:///d:/final/CMGROUPS/backend/src/routes/orders.js#18-36) silently returns 0 if product has no points set (Medium)
**File:** [orders.js](file:///d:/final/CMGROUPS/backend/src/routes/orders.js) lines 18–35, [referralHelper.js](file:///d:/final/CMGROUPS/backend/src/utils/referralHelper.js) lines 8–19  
**Problem:** If a product's `referrerPoints` is `null` or `0`, [calculateReferralReward](file:///d:/final/CMGROUPS/backend/src/utils/referralHelper.js#3-21) returns `{referrerPoints: 0, refereePoints: 0}`. If ALL items in an order have no points configured, the referral reward is 0 and no Referral record is created — silently, with no feedback. This is by design but means no fallback to the global [ReferralSettings](file:///d:/final/CMGROUPS/frontend/src/lib/api.js#425-426) default.

**Current behavior:** If you use a referral code but buy products without `referrerPoints` set, neither the referrer nor the buyer gets anything, and the [Referral](file:///d:/final/CMGROUPS/frontend/src/lib/api.js#423-424) record is never created.

**Fix (Option A):** Fall back to `ReferralSettings.pointsPerProductPurchase` if a product has no specific `referrerPoints`. This is the most complete fix.

#### Bug 5 — Services: `WalletTransaction` records NOT created for referral credits
**File:** [services.js](file:///d:/final/CMGROUPS/backend/src/routes/services.js) ~lines 522–533  
**Problem:** The service referral logic credits the wallets:
```js
await tx.user.update({ ... walletBalance: { increment: rewardAmount } });
await tx.user.update({ ... walletBalance: { increment: refereePoints } });
```
But unlike the courses flow, there are **no `WalletTransaction` records** created. So the user's wallet shows the balance but their transaction history shows nothing.

**Fix:** Add `walletTransaction.create` calls for both referrer and referee (same as the courses flow).

#### Bug 6 — Courses: Referral record has no `WalletTransaction` for referee
**File:** [courses.js](file:///d:/final/CMGROUPS/backend/src/routes/courses.js) line 372–373  
**Status:** Actually ✅ — referee wallet transaction IS created on line 373. This is fine.

#### Bug 7 — Products: `referralEligibleAt` cron job not implemented
**File:** [orders.js](file:///d:/final/CMGROUPS/backend/src/routes/orders.js) — returnable items set `referralEligibleAt` but no cron processes it  
**Problem:** When an order has returnable items, the code sets `referralEligibleAt` to `deliveredAt + returnWindowDays`. But there is no cron job that processes orders where `referralEligibleAt < now()` to distribute the referral reward. These orders get lost.  
Check: `backend/src/cron/` — let me verify.

